6. **TP (Critical)** - `InvalidRequestFilter.containsTraversal()` at line 131: Default NORMAL mode only calls `isNormalized()`, missing encoded period/slash checks that only STRICT mode provides, leaving gap for %2e%2e traversal bypass.

The core vulnerability pattern is consistent with known Shiro CVEs (CVE-2020-11989, CVE-2020-13933): the filter validates one path representation while routing uses a normalized/different representation.
